description:
The PBS NewsHour for Sunday, March 9, 2014, standard definition

Description:
On Sunday's program, what's believed to be debris from the missing Malaysia airlines jet is discovered in waters off Vietnam. We get perspective on the state of airport security. Chris Matthews of the Wall Street Journal gives us the latest on the trial of Osama bin Laden's son-in-law. And, in our signature segment, a look at an unlikely coalition between frackers and environmentalists in Pennsylvania.
